gst-plugin-pylon (0.3.0-0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added - Support to access stream grabber parameters via stream:: prefix
  * Added - Bayer 8bit video data support
  * Added - Add property to configure camera from a pylon feature stream file ( pfs-location=<filename> )
  * Added - Support to build gst-plugin-pylon as monorepo subproject to test against upcoming changes in gstreamer monorepo
  * Added - Add pygobject example to access camera and stream grabber features in the folder examples
  * Changed - Remove fixed grab timeout of 5s. pylonsrc will now wait forever. If required timeout/underrun detection can be handled in the gstreamer pipeline. ( e.g. via queue underrun )
  * Changed - Remove limititation to only map features that are streamable Effect is that now all accessible features of a camera are mapped to gstreamer properties
  * Changed - Output more information in case of missing selection of a camera. Now: serial number, model name and user defined name.
  * Changed - Run all tests in github actions
  * Fixed - Allow loading of default user set on some early Basler USB3Vision cameras

 -- Thies Möller thies.moeller@baslerweb.com  Tue, 13 Sep 2022 00:00:00 -0700

